communities.name: Ashby Commons
communities.desc: Live affordably in the heart of charming Easton. Walk to absolutely everything - dining, shopping, the theater. Explore opportunity zone investment possibilities.

communities.name: Clarksburg Town Center
communities.desc: What a neighborhood was meant to be. Shop for local produce at the Clarksburg Farmer’s Market. Cheer on the Tiger Shark Swim Team. Or just relax at the local café.

communities.name: Eastchurch
communities.desc: Equal parts urban vibe and village charm. History, culture, shopping and dining – it’s all steps from your front door in downtown historic Frederick.

communities.name: Easton Village
communities.desc: Kayaking in the morning, lounging poolside in the afternoon, walking with friends to dine in Easton in the evening. Chesapeake village charm on the Tred Avon River. Enjoy!

communities.name: Eva Mar Farms
communities.desc: With the majority of the lots sited adjacent to either woods or open space, the community offers country living minutes from the restaurants and retail offerings of Bel Air.
communities.address: 1626 Eva Mare Blvd, Bel Air MD 21015

communities.name: Forest Knoll
communities.desc: Take a deep breath. Explore miles of nearby trails and parks. A small enclave of single family homes just waiting for your family to enjoy.

communities.name: Georgia Row
communities.desc: Plant your roots. Conquer a commute. Enjoy the perks of an established neighborhood as you watch the redevelopment of Walter Reed across the street. (And, just minutes to Metro.)

communities.name: Greenleigh
communities.desc: Life in the suburbs. Reimagined. An upscale, urban-inspired community offering the perfect blend of location and luxury when you don’t want to compromise.

communities.name: Lake Linganore
communities.desc: Carved by nature and built for today’s living. Get in on the lake lifestyle. Take in the scenic views. Drop in a fishing line. Explore the miles of trails. It’s all here.

communities.name: Landsdale
communities.desc: Life happens at Landsdale. Connect with your neighbors. Unwind in the world-class amenity park. Or just sit back and enjoy the breathtaking views of Sugarloaf Mountain.

communities.name: Marshall Grove Estates
communities.desc: Come out and play. Jump on a trail. Run Fido in the dog park. Join the pick-up game on the sports field. Or relax with our Potomac River views. It’s all here.

communities.name: Mill Creek
communities.desc: Enjoy stunning new homes situated between Baltimore and D.C in the River Hill School District,  offering private luxury and comfort adjacent to preserved open space and a State Park with scenic views in all directions.

communities.name: Morgan Creek
communities.desc: Looking for the perfect blend of serenity and convenience? Morgan Creek’s 1 acre homesites are surrounded by mature forests yet minutes from the conveniences of downtown Eldersburg.

communities.name: Odenton Station
communities.desc: Commuting has never been easier. Live steps from the Odenton Marc Station and the shops of the Odenton Town Center.

communities.name: Parkside at Warfield
communities.desc: Deeply rooted in small-town charm, blended with new world amenities. Its unbeatable skyline view and convenience to commuter routes make it an ideal place to live life.

communities.name: Roland Heights
communities.desc: Not ready for suburban life? Be a part of the best of urban living. Walk to everything you need. You and the kids will enjoy the highly ranked neighborhood elementary school.

communities.name: The Preserve at Timber Ridge
communities.desc: Into the great(est) wide open. At Timber Ridge we have acres of open space, an impressive trail system and loads of outdoor play spaces. Take a deep breath. That’s fresh air. Nice, huh?
communities.address: 2405 Marshall Hall Road, Bryans Road, MD  20616

communities.name: The Reserve at Black Rock
communities.desc: The ideal fusion of cosmopolitan and country living. The rare opportunity to design and build the home you want on a lot where there’s room to live.

communities.name: Watershed
communities.desc: Discover your watershed moment. With miles of trails, a modern clubhouse, bike pump track, movies in the amphitheatre and the 12,000 acre Wildlife Refuge next door, it’s up to you.

communities.name: Willowshire
communities.desc: Ten minutes from Clarkesville, yet quietly tucked in a wooded setting amidst Howard County pastoral farms.  A peaceful retreat from the everyday bustle and commotion.

communities.name: Bryans Village
communities.desc: Come home to Potomac River views. Unwind with friends in the community park. Get your sweat on with our trail network and exercise stations. Minutes to National Harbor nightlife.

communities.name: Eagles Rest II
communities.desc: A community with room to breathe. Featuring an enclave of beautiful homes a couple of minutes off of 95 in a quiet countryside setting.

communities.name: Elkridge Woods
communities.desc: Centrally located in just minutes off of 95 in Howard County’s highly desirable school district.  Enjoy living in a beautiful single family home close to all the amenities of Columbia and Ellicott City.

communities.name: Tanyard Shores
communities.desc: Launch your next adventure here. Walk or bike the miles of shoreline trails, set a crab pot at the community marina, take a spin on the bike pump track (ok, maybe your kids will).
communities.address: Freeman Shores Rd & Marley Neck Blvd

communities.name: Walker Meadows
communities.desc: Awaken your sense of adventure with hiking, fishing, camping, canoeing and more right in your own backyard. Large lot living with the academic advantage of our highly rated schools. (180)

communities.name: Anchor Point
communities.desc: Enjoy a small town lifestyle surprisingly close to the Washington metropolitan area. Stroll along the Village Green, experience the beauty of nature walking or biking the rail trail. Relax with friends at a local eatery.
communities.address: Dr. Andrews Way, Indian Head, MD

communities.name: Brookestone
communities.desc: An enclave of townhomes with big community amenities. Jump on a trail and see where it takes you. Harvest herbs from the community garden. Enjoy the kids walking to school.

communities.name: Retreat at Westfields
communities.desc: Built around a neighborhood pond, Retreat at Westfields fosters gathering whether at the overlook, formal green, picnic lawns, playground or pavilion - all convenient to the lively Westfields Center.

communities.name: St. Paul's College
communities.desc: The vibe and convenience of Brookland city living in a hard-to-find park-like setting. Monroe Street Market and Brookland Metro are just steps away.

communities.name: Sunstone
communities.desc: Every day is play day.  Swing, bike or grab Rover and frolic in the one-of-a-kind Bark Park. Or, indulge your mind, body and spirit in the woods out your back door.

communities.name: The Pennant
communities.desc: Unparalleled Fells Point living. Contemporary meets luxury at this walk-to-everything location.  Water taxi to vibrant shops and eateries or relax at home on your rooftop terrace.

communities.name: Woods Edge
communities.desc: Come out to play. Pick herbs from the garden. Challenge yourself on the exercise stations. Gather your friends for a picnic on the green. Everything here is a little more fun.

communities.name: Merrilee
communities.desc: Enjoy your amazing commute living in our luxurious apartment homes next to the Dunn Loring Metro. Walk to the restaurants and excitement of the close by Mosaic district.

communities.name: The Elms at PSTA
communities.desc: 630 vibrant homes in Montgomery County’s growing biotechnology hub. This community will enjoy on-site amenities and is in easy walking distance to offices, schools and shopping.
communities.address: Intersection of Great Seneca Highway and Key West Avenue

communities.name: Arnold Overlook
communities.desc: Remember the good old days when kids walked to school? Well, they’re here. Single family living in a natural setting with Arnold Elementary in your backyard.

communities.name: Century Row
communities.desc: Urban living in Germantown. Stroll to the town center. Or stay at home and jump on the fitness stations, play catch with the kids or join neighbors for a cocktail in the plaza.

communities.name: Crest of Alexandria
communities.desc: 55+. You’ve earned it. A space just for you. With curated amenities and activities like your very own clubhouse and pickle ball court and neighborhood happy hours. Enjoy!

communities.name: Featherstone Square
communities.desc: New luxury in well-established Woodbridge. Enjoy this convenient, entertainment-friendly neighborhood just 1 mile from the Woodbridge VRE station.

communities.name: Gibson's Grant
communities.desc: Unwind every day on the Chester River. Community happy hours, world-class bird watching, kayaking out your front door. Water’s Edge – the final neighborhood is now selling.

communities.name: Liberty
communities.desc: Tired of the same old, same old? Live, shop and play in a vibrant urban village uniquely situated on the grounds of the old Lorton Prison.

communities.name: Oakview Village
communities.desc: A home that's never far away from everyday life. Discover a spacious community with a resident plaza, large open green space and easy access to desirable destinations.
communities.address: 7802 Five Oaks Court, Glen Burnie, MD 21061

communities.name: Pondview
communities.desc: What to do…What to do. Drop a line in the pond. Ride the Radio Flyer down the sledding hill. Join your neighbors for s’mores by the fire pit. And so much more.

communities.name: Shannon's Glen
communities.desc: Commute no more. Walk, bike or even scooter to work at National Business Park and NSA.  You’ll have more time to unwind by the pool or kick a ball with the kids at the playground.

communities.name: Severn Hollow
communities.desc: Location, Location, Location.  Be a commuter, shopper, diner or even player minutes from home.

communities.name: The Preserve at Westfields
communities.desc: Relax at home with neighbors by the pond or on your rooftop deck. Shopping and dining surround you in Chantilly and Reston or hop on the nearby Silver Line for a quick trip to Tysons.

communities.name: The Village at Arundel Mills
communities.desc: Suburban? Urban? All we know is that you can walk to absolutely everything from your new neighborhood - dining (20+ restaurants), shopping (200+ stores) and entertainment venues.
